## What I Built for Synergy

### 1. plato-jetson: SonarVisionRoom (89 lines)
- Underwater room class extending Evennia Room
- Auto-generates descriptions from sonar pings
- 5-room dive chain installed in the MUD
- `sonarping` command for player interaction
- Physics: Jerlov attenuation, fish schools, seabed features, bioluminescence

### 2. open-agents: sonar-vision-tool.ts (136 lines)
- Full TypeScript tool with Zod schema
- Three actions: infer, physics, health
- Deterministic physics (attenuation, visibility, sound speed by depth)
- Server connect for inference, fallback for offline mode
- Registerable with ToolSet via registerSonarVisionTool()

## Synergy Status
- **6 repos now interconnected** (sonar-vision, marine-gpu-edge, jepa-perception-lab,
  holodeck-rust, plato-jetson, open-agents)
- Each repo has a distinct role in the pipeline
- Fleet-wide pattern: physics data flows through FLUX bytecodes, sonar frames through MEP,
  latents through JEPA, rooms through MUD, dashboards through WebSocket

